    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened and starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>to the pan with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> ground coriander</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil then cook for 3 min or until reduced to a curry-like consistency</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once reduced, top the<strong> </strong>sauce with your <strong>diced pollock </strong>(unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the pollock is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Fluff the<strong> cauliflower rice</strong> with a fork, stir through the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> coriander cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pollock is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and stir in your <strong>clotted cream </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> butter pollock</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir gently so that your fish doesn't break apart!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/butter-pollock-with-coriander-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>butter pollock </strong>over the <strong>coriander cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
